1.title: Episode #1.1
1.plot: JP plans a performance in the Heights, while his mother puts the pressure on to help out with the bills. Jimmy tries out for a competitive baseball team. Animosity between Eliza and Reyna escalates until they meet at JP's show.

2.title: Episode #1.2
2.plot: Ludwin and his girlfriend are back together, but will Frankie be able to let go of her crush? Fall out from the fight at Apt 78 continues and JP promises to bring the group back together. Will it happen in time for his big show?

3.title: Episode #1.3
3.plot: Drama with Ludwin and Diana escalates into a huge fight, and Frankie thinks about telling Ludwin how she feels about him. Brothers Rico and Fred wonder how they will pay the bills when their mom moves out.

4.title: Episode #1.4
4.plot: Frankie is falling for Ludwin, but with everything he's dealing with, will he be able to give her what she wants? A fight between Rico and Fred reveals deep issues between the two. Will they make up in time for mom to move out?

5.title: Episode #1.5
5.plot: With Ludwin's brother in trouble, he leans on Frankie for support and she knows just how to cheer him up. After a huge fight with her sister, Reyna makes a big decision. JP's mom asks him to pay the electric bill this month.

6.title: Episode #1.6
6.plot: Jimmy is forced to choose between baseball and his job. Will he follow his dream or face reality? Reyna is pushed to continue her music, but will her fears get in the way? Ludwin gives out his number behind Frankie's back.

7.title: Episode #1.7
7.plot: Frankie and Fred organize an event downtown to showcase their friends' talents. Reyna is excited for her first singing performance, but her parents' divorce looms over her. Jimmy and Eliza's relationship begins to unravel.

8.title: Episode #1.8
8.plot: Taylor and Reyna stage an intervention with Frankie about her relationship with Ludwin. After taking a break, Jimmy and Eliza meet to decide whats next. JP meets with a rep from a record label. Could this be his big break?

9.title: Episode #1.9
9.plot: Frankie agrees to go on a date with Taylor's friend. Will it make Ludwin jealous? With her parents divorce, Reyna lost contact with her father but tries to fix their relationship. Rico has his final acting class performance.

10.title: Episode #1.10
10.plot: Frankie learns Diana has been talking smack about her on twitter. Will the two come face to face at Ludwin's upcoming art show? Jimmy ties up loose ends before he leaves for Florida. JP scores an audition for a national tour.

11.title: Episode #1.11
11.plot: Ludwin decides to leave the Heights and struggles with how he will break it to Frankie. Reyna seeks independence and makes some difficult choices. At a crossroads in his career, JP hears back about the national tour.

imdb.plot outline: Follows a group of best friends living, working and playing in the gritty, diverse New York neighborhood of Washington Heights. Though fiercely proud of where they come from, the show charts the triumphs and pitfalls as the cast struggle to push past the confines of their upbringing in order to carve out bright futures for themselves. Despite the obstacles that threaten to stand in the way of their respective pursuits (professional baseball, hip hop artist, spoken-word poet), they always have each others backs. The Heights is a celebration of friendship, neighborhood pride, and making your way in life while having a good time along the way.
